===Noun===
'''theion'''  (''plural:'' uncountable)
# (''archaic''): [[sulfur]]
# (''archaic''): [[fire]], especially in the context of [[fire and brimstone]]
# (''archaic''): the [[divine]], especially a divine fire
#: Divinum, in Greek is '''theion''', Divine. This term in Scripture: 1. Sometimes notes the divine essence, or God-head itself, to '''theion''' heinai homioi ("that the God head is like to" -- Acts 17:29).[http://www.naphtali.com/jusextrc.htm] 

